            <title>[IMAGING-190] ImageDataReader.decompress() overwrites its input</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/IMAGING-190</link>
                <project id="12313421" key="IMAGING">Commons Imaging</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The ImageDataReader.decompress() method rewrites its input data if the fill order is set to FILL_ORDER_VALUE_REVERSED.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;However AFAICT the fill order is not then updated, so calling the method mulitple times will redo the conversion.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The method should probably use a new array if the output has to be reversed.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
